================================================================================
5. REMEDIATION DECISIONS
================================================================================

ISSUE 1: NULL customer_id in Orders (~2%)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Decision: FLAG (do not exclude)

Rationale:
- 300 orders worth ~$165K in revenue should not be discarded
- Create is_customer_matched flag for segmentation analysis
- Include in revenue reporting, exclude from customer-level metrics
- Investigate source system to prevent future occurrences

Implementation:
  ALTER TABLE orders ADD COLUMN is_customer_matched BOOLEAN;
  UPDATE orders SET is_customer_matched = (customer_id IS NOT NULL);


ISSUE 2: Impossible Dates (delivered < ordered) (~1%)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Decision: FLAG + EXCLUDE from time-based analysis

Rationale:
- These records corrupt delivery time calculations
- Cannot be reliably corrected without source data investigation
- Revenue data is still valid

Implementation:
  ALTER TABLE orders ADD COLUMN has_valid_dates BOOLEAN;
  UPDATE orders SET has_valid_dates = NOT (delivered_date < order_date);

  -- For delivery time analysis, filter:
  WHERE has_valid_dates = TRUE


ISSUE 3: NULL return_received_date (~12%)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Decision: NO ACTION REQUIRED

Rationale:
- These represent returns currently in transit (status = 'In Transit')
- Business-expected NULL - not a data quality issue
- Will be populated when items arrive at warehouse


ISSUE 4: Statistical Outliers in Order Values
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Decision: RETAIN ALL

Rationale:
- High-value orders are legitimate transactions (verified against products)
- Electronics, bulk orders, and premium shipping explain the distribution
- Excluding would bias revenue analysis by ~$1.2M
- Median-based metrics already account for skewness


ISSUE 5: High Stockout Rate (62.75%)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Decision: ESCALATE FOR BUSINESS REVIEW

Rationale:
- This is not a data quality issue - it's an operational finding
- Inventory tracking only covers 80 of 480 products (16.7%)
- The tracked products appear to be high-velocity items
- Requires supply chain / inventory management investigation


